1
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:23,941
<i>That attorney gets jealous easily.</i>

2
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:25,234
I wasn't doing anything wrong.

3
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:27,236
<i>It's Sir Steven.</i>
<i>I hope I get my job back.</i>

4
00:00:27,319 --> 00:00:28,821
I caught her just as you walked in.

5
00:00:28,904 --> 00:00:29,947
She told me the same thing.

6
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,115
<i>Has Steven given you your pay?</i>

7
00:00:31,198 --> 00:00:32,450
- Yes, sir.
- Go home early.

8
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:33,784
- <i>Treat your family.</i>
- Get dressed.

9
00:00:33,868 --> 00:00:35,578
We'll find you a prosthetic leg.

10
00:00:35,661 --> 00:00:37,872
You're fired!
You let a criminal into our house!

11
00:00:37,955 --> 00:00:39,331
I have a bad feeling about this.

12
00:00:39,415 --> 00:00:41,917
- Why didn't you tell me?
- I'm a victim, sir, not a criminal.

13
00:00:42,001 --> 00:00:43,419
<i>What else aren't you telling me?</i>

14
00:00:43,502 --> 00:00:45,963
Can I ask a question?
I'm looking for a foreigner.

15
00:00:46,046 --> 00:00:47,173
That building
where all the foreigners live,

16
00:00:47,256 --> 00:00:48,257
that's where he stays.

17
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:51,802
- <i>Stop pretending, Yana!</i>
- <i>I'm not that woman!</i>

18
00:00:51,886 --> 00:00:54,638
I gave you this in Morocco
when you manipulated me.

19
00:00:54,722 --> 00:00:56,223
I'm going to tell them the truth.

20
00:00:56,307 --> 00:00:57,600
Wait. Wait.

21
00:00:57,683 --> 00:01:00,686
You got out of prison because of me.

22
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:05,941
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

23
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:46,774
I needed to die...

24
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,986
so that you could live.

25
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:53,489
- Why did you do that?
- Because you are a good person.

26
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:57,451
Because you weren't supposed
to be in prison.

27
00:01:57,535 --> 00:01:58,744
But you left me.

28
00:01:59,662 --> 00:02:00,663
You ran away.

29
00:02:00,746 --> 00:02:03,040
You pinned all your crimes on me.

30
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,292
And now, you're living in luxury!

31
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,795
You don't know what I'm going through.

32
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:09,880
Is it worse than what I've been through?

33
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:12,842
This? Huh?

34
00:02:14,885 --> 00:02:15,886
This?

35
00:02:17,429 --> 00:02:19,265
Is this what you went through?

36
00:02:23,561 --> 00:02:25,771
I gave myself to Ace...

37
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:28,691
...so you could be pardoned.

38
00:02:28,774 --> 00:02:30,484
Even though it's hard...

39
00:02:31,026 --> 00:02:32,361
I endured it.

40
00:02:33,279 --> 00:02:34,780
Just so you could be free.

41
00:02:34,864 --> 00:02:36,991
So that you could get your life back.

42
00:02:37,074 --> 00:02:39,493
You're just clearing your conscience.

43
00:02:40,119 --> 00:02:41,620
Even if you died,

44
00:02:41,704 --> 00:02:44,582
you'd never make up for your sins.

45
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,502
Is that so?

46
00:02:48,586 --> 00:02:50,212
Then what more do you want?

47
00:02:50,296 --> 00:02:53,757
For me to apologize? I'm sorry I hurt you,
I'm sorry I did you wrong.

48
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:55,259
What do you want?

49
00:02:55,342 --> 00:02:58,220
Tell that tale of yours to your husband,

50
00:02:58,304 --> 00:03:00,681
to his family, and to everyone downstairs.

51
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:04,643
Only then can I move on.

52
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,187
Do you know what they'll do to you?

53
00:03:07,271 --> 00:03:08,898
They're going to kill you.

54
00:03:10,608 --> 00:03:13,193
Because your life is useless to them.

55
00:03:13,277 --> 00:03:14,904
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

56
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:17,281
- Ace.
- Mama and Papa are looking for you.

57
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:20,451
I'll stay here for now.
Mama's suffocating me.

58
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:21,911
Anyway, have you seen Gem?

59
00:03:25,122 --> 00:03:26,206
She went to your room.

60
00:03:26,874 --> 00:03:28,500
She said she was going to get changed.

61
00:03:30,294 --> 00:03:31,545
I'll just get her,
then we'll talk, okay?

62
00:03:31,629 --> 00:03:32,463
Okay.

63
00:03:33,047 --> 00:03:34,965
Hey, watch it.

64
00:03:35,049 --> 00:03:37,217
- Papa might see you.
Thank you, Ace.

65
00:03:45,893 --> 00:03:48,270
- We're not done talking!
Get out.

66
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:49,980


67
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:51,649

We've already discussed this, Michael,

68
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:53,567
and I don't think I'll be able
to help you.

69
00:03:53,651 --> 00:03:55,110
I don't know
if you've heard the latest.

70
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:56,862
You heard what happened to Luis?

71
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:59,907
Teo, Ace is coming. Hide!

72
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,116
- No, we should face him...
No!

73
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,618
- ...so you admit the truth.
He wouldn't understand!

74
00:04:02,701 --> 00:04:04,536
You don't know who the Veronas really are.

75
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:06,413
They'll kill you and your family.

76
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:09,917
Teo, they're going to kill me.

77
00:04:11,627 --> 00:04:13,420
- Thank you. Have a good day.
You're welcome.

78
00:04:13,504 --> 00:04:16,507


79
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:21,887


80
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:29,395
What the hell's taking you so long?

81
00:04:29,478 --> 00:04:31,939
I was just fixing
my makeup and hair.

82
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:37,695
Well, fix your dress while you're at it.

83
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:41,949
Why? Is there a problem with my dress?

84
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:43,867


85
00:04:47,579 --> 00:04:49,039


86
00:04:49,123 --> 00:04:51,375
Why are you so desperate for attention?

87
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:52,918
What are you saying?

88
00:04:54,086 --> 00:04:55,629

This is what you want, right?

89
00:04:55,713 --> 00:04:57,256
- To show your body off?
Love, stop!

90
00:04:57,339 --> 00:04:58,590

Show it to all of our guests.

91
00:04:58,674 --> 00:04:59,758
Don't touch me!

92
00:05:00,426 --> 00:05:01,927


93
00:05:02,011 --> 00:05:03,178


94
00:05:06,432 --> 00:05:09,601
-

95
00:05:09,685 --> 00:05:12,855
Wear that one. That's more appropriate.

96
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:14,356
And fix yourself, please?

97
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:18,152
Don't you dare embarrass me again.

98
00:05:21,572 --> 00:05:24,116


99
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:35,335


100
00:05:54,897 --> 00:05:58,192


101
00:05:58,275 --> 00:06:00,986


102
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:22,883


103
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,849


104
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:36,647


105
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:58,669


106
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:06,760
Uh, Attorney Alberto?

107
00:07:08,512 --> 00:07:09,847
- Attorney Alberto.
Yes?

108
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:13,809
Hello, good evening.
I'm Larajean.

109
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:16,895
I wrote you a letter before in Morocco.

110
00:07:16,979 --> 00:07:20,232
It was about... a request of mine

111
00:07:20,315 --> 00:07:24,027
about the Filipino who was imprisoned,
Teo Crisanto.

112
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:27,614
Dear, I receive a lot of letters, so...

113
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:30,242

I'm sorry, I can't remember you.

114
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:33,036


115
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:40,460
Tell your friend... to savor and to enjoy,

116
00:07:40,544 --> 00:07:43,130
and to cherish
this second chance at life, okay?

117
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,048
And tell him not to get
in trouble anymore.

118
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,342
Yes, sir. Thank you again.

119
00:07:47,426 --> 00:07:49,428
- Thank you. Good evening.
Yeah. We have to go.

120
00:07:52,931 --> 00:07:54,516


121
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,185
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

122
00:08:01,607 --> 00:08:04,276
Teo! Have you confirmed it?

123
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:06,612
Ma'am Gem is Yana, right?

124
00:08:06,695 --> 00:08:09,198
Neither Ma'am Gem nor Yana
has anything to do with this.

125
00:08:11,116 --> 00:08:12,492
And I'll stop this now.

126
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:16,163
Wait.

127
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:19,833
Are you really the reason
why I got out of Morocco?

128
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:21,919
Yeah!

129
00:08:22,002 --> 00:08:24,338
Attorney Alberto's here,
you should've confirmed

130
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:26,048
what I've been telling you for a long time

131
00:08:26,131 --> 00:08:29,468
that I was the one who looked for ways
to free you from prison.

132
00:08:31,762 --> 00:08:34,514
It's a pity, he just left with his wife.

133
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,150


134
00:08:46,443 --> 00:08:47,486
You still awake?

135
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:50,155
I'm still reviewing.

136
00:08:50,239 --> 00:08:53,867
We listed our names
for the placement exam.

137
00:08:53,951 --> 00:08:56,370
- Mm-hmm?
- I have to pass that, Teo.

138
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:59,831
And when I graduate,
I'll study to become a lawyer.

139
00:08:59,915 --> 00:09:02,542
I'll take up legal management like Ronnie.

140
00:09:02,626 --> 00:09:04,169
Wow! Come here.

141
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:08,548
I'll save up for that, okay?

142
00:09:08,632 --> 00:09:10,676
I'll do everything
so you can finish your studies

143
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,552
and make all your dreams come true.

144
00:09:12,636 --> 00:09:14,388
- Hm?
- Thank you!

145
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:23,480
Pa.

146
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:28,568
It's Nikolas's birthday.
He had <i>pansit </i>and drinks.

147
00:09:28,652 --> 00:09:30,862
Issay, put it in the fridge
so it doesn't go bad.

148
00:09:30,946 --> 00:09:32,197
We can eat it tomorrow.

149
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:36,118
You look like you have been drinking.

150
00:09:39,413 --> 00:09:41,498
I know what you look like when you lose.

151
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:45,002
- It was just 800.
- 800? Are you trivializing 800?

152
00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:46,545
That's a few kilograms of rice, Pa.

153
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:50,257
We've been through this before, Pa.
Haven't you learned anything?

154
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:52,926
Do you think I haven't
learned anything at my age?

155
00:09:54,511 --> 00:09:56,179
Besides, why are we talking about me?

156
00:09:57,431 --> 00:10:00,350
You're the one who looks troubled.

157
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:05,063
That's exactly it.

158
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:08,900
She confessed.

159
00:10:10,694 --> 00:10:12,946
Sir Ace's wife, Gem Verona?

160
00:10:13,739 --> 00:10:14,698
She's Yana.

161
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:19,286
Why don't you report
that fake and deceitful person?

162
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:21,288
She said she's the one
who arranged my pardon.

163
00:10:22,372 --> 00:10:25,834
She said she needed to die
so I could live.

164
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:29,004
That damned woman is a complete liar!

165
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:31,715
You know what? You should report it.

166
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:33,175
It's not that easy, Pa.

167
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:35,469
Her husband beats her.

168
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:36,887
The revelation would put her in danger.

169
00:10:37,387 --> 00:10:38,347
You know what, son?

170
00:10:39,348 --> 00:10:41,516
It's best not to get involved.

171
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:44,936
Let them be. You have separate lives now.

172
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,772
Don't torture yourself anymore.

173
00:10:48,106 --> 00:10:50,942
- I'll rest now, Pa.
- Okay, go to sleep.

174
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:14,383
Your total due for this quarter

175
00:11:14,466 --> 00:11:18,345
is 250,000 pesos, sir,
including penalties.

176
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:20,055
I don't have that much money.

177
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:22,140
Is there a discount

178
00:11:22,224 --> 00:11:26,645
or an amnesty program I can use?

179
00:11:26,728 --> 00:11:28,230
If you settle this week,

180
00:11:28,313 --> 00:11:30,732
you might get an approval
from the City Treasurer.

181
00:11:30,816 --> 00:11:32,692
The interest will also be waived.

182
00:11:32,776 --> 00:11:35,153
That's almost 100,000 pesos, sir.

183
00:11:35,237 --> 00:11:37,030
So I just need to pay 150,000 pesos?

184
00:11:37,114 --> 00:11:38,365
More or less, yes.

185
00:11:38,448 --> 00:11:41,118
But immediate payment in full is required.

186
00:11:42,244 --> 00:11:43,787
I have...

187
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:46,706
Two thousand, five hundred pesos.
This is all I can give today.

188
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:48,250
- Sir--
- Could I pay a down payment,

189
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,626
then pay in installments?

190
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:51,628
Sir, you can't pay property tax
in installments.

191
00:11:51,711 --> 00:11:53,088
Full payment is required.

192
00:12:16,862 --> 00:12:18,613
- Teo.
- Sir?

193
00:12:20,574 --> 00:12:21,908
Not there, I'll put this in the front.

194
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:30,500
- Be careful.
- Yes, sir.

195
00:12:31,168 --> 00:12:32,210
Ma'am.

196
00:12:36,047 --> 00:12:37,132
Ma'am.

197
00:12:37,215 --> 00:12:38,383
About last night...

198
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:43,180
I...

199
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:53,690
What is it?

200
00:13:02,741 --> 00:13:03,700
Let's go!

201
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:08,830
What is that?

202
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:11,958
Uh...

203
00:13:12,042 --> 00:13:14,085
I found this while cleaning the car.

204
00:13:14,169 --> 00:13:16,713
I was just returning it to Ma'am Gem.
Ma'am, is this yours?

205
00:13:19,174 --> 00:13:21,092
I didn't even realize
it's missing.

206
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:23,303
Love, put that on
so you won't lose it again.

207
00:13:23,386 --> 00:13:24,596
Isn't that expensive?

208
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,515
Yeah, it's priceless.

209
00:13:32,187 --> 00:13:33,855
What are we waiting for? Let's go.

210
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:34,940
All right, sir.

211
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:38,902
Take me to the police station.

212
00:13:38,985 --> 00:13:40,320
I have stuff
to attend to right away.

213
00:13:40,403 --> 00:13:41,404
Okay, sir.

214
00:14:07,013 --> 00:14:09,516
<i>Pa? Daniela Ordoñez</i>
<i>is no longer here.</i>

215
00:14:09,599 --> 00:14:11,434
She's in the Ministry
of Justice as we speak!

216
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:12,602
What?

217
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:16,398
<i>Daniela Ordoñez is holding</i>
<i>a press conference right now.</i>

218
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:19,484
<i>She's allegedly an overseas</i>
<i>Filipina worker sent to Morocco</i>

219
00:14:19,568 --> 00:14:21,027
<i>as an illegal recruit.</i>

220
00:14:21,111 --> 00:14:22,362
<i>Let's watch this.</i>

221
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,114
Pa?

222
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:26,032
<i>Ordoñez is having a press con!</i>

223
00:14:26,116 --> 00:14:27,158
I'll talk to you later.

224
00:14:29,828 --> 00:14:32,872
<i>I just want to make an appeal</i>

225
00:14:32,956 --> 00:14:34,833
<i>to be a state witness.</i>

226
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:40,422
<i>I know who the masterminds</i>
<i>behind this operation are.</i>

227
00:14:40,505 --> 00:14:43,133
<i>I've been traveling for three years.</i>

228
00:14:43,216 --> 00:14:48,597
<i>I escort</i>
<i>the illegal recruits to Singapore.</i>

229
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:52,767
<i>When they get there,</i>
<i>other people take them.</i>

230
00:14:52,851 --> 00:14:55,020
<i>We have an agency.</i>

231
00:14:56,646 --> 00:14:58,481
<i>But that's just a front.</i>

232
00:14:59,107 --> 00:15:01,234
<i>I already told them the names.</i>

233
00:15:03,486 --> 00:15:05,614
<i>The police also confirmed that</i>

234
00:15:05,697 --> 00:15:07,699
<i>they've gone missing...</i>

235
00:15:07,782 --> 00:15:09,034
<i>until now.</i>

236
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:12,078
<i>What agency are you</i>
<i>talking about, and who owns it?</i>

237
00:15:12,162 --> 00:15:13,913
<i>Al Khail Manpower.</i>

238
00:15:13,997 --> 00:15:17,042
<i>But they also go by different names.</i>

239
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:20,128
<i>But they all have the same owner.</i>

240
00:15:20,211 --> 00:15:21,671
<i>The Veronas.</i>

241
00:15:22,213 --> 00:15:24,299
<i>What evidence</i>
<i>do you have to prove that it's them?</i>

242
00:15:24,382 --> 00:15:28,053
<i>I've known it for a while now,</i>
<i>even though I can't see them.</i>

243
00:15:28,136 --> 00:15:32,182
<i>But when I got caught,</i>
<i>he called me himself.</i>

244
00:15:33,350 --> 00:15:37,312
<i>Judge Verona told me</i>
<i>that he would help me...</i>

245
00:15:37,395 --> 00:15:39,648
<i>if I kept quiet.</i>

246
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:42,275
<i>Do you have a recording? Messages?</i>

247
00:15:42,359 --> 00:15:44,527
<i>We already have her device.</i>

248
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:47,197
<i>We're currently verifying</i>

249
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,157
<i>all the call logs, timestamps,</i>

250
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,700
<i>and all the communications.</i>

251
00:15:50,784 --> 00:15:52,702
<i>I just want all of this to end.</i>

252
00:15:53,787 --> 00:15:55,705
<i>I don't want anyone else to disappear.</i>

253
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:58,708


254
00:15:58,792 --> 00:16:00,835
We need to fix this right now.

255
00:16:00,919 --> 00:16:02,796
We draft a counter-affidavit.

256
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:06,466
Perjury, extortion,
falsification of charges.

257
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:08,218
We bury her credibility.

258
00:16:08,301 --> 00:16:11,429
No credibility, no case.

259
00:16:11,513 --> 00:16:13,223
I just spoke to Chief Garcia.

260
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,309
And he told me that he would
take care of the phone calls

261
00:16:16,393 --> 00:16:17,519
that woman is so proud of.

262
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:19,562
That bitch is done!

263
00:16:19,646 --> 00:16:21,648
If you had let me
fix it in the first place,

264
00:16:21,731 --> 00:16:23,066
this wouldn't have happened!

265
00:16:23,149 --> 00:16:25,068
Blame game is for losers!

266
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:26,444
Focus, Ace!

267
00:16:26,528 --> 00:16:28,863
Our emotions
are just going to ruin us right now.

268
00:16:28,947 --> 00:16:30,615
Then we can make her recant!

269
00:16:30,699 --> 00:16:31,991
Threaten her!

270
00:16:32,075 --> 00:16:34,452
Make her realize what happens
to the people who cross us!

271
00:16:34,536 --> 00:16:36,413
Not this time, Ace!

272
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:38,832
You are going to be taking
bigger responsibilities

273
00:16:38,915 --> 00:16:41,084
and duties for this company
beginning today.

274
00:16:41,793 --> 00:16:44,045
But for now,
your father and I will deal

275
00:16:44,129 --> 00:16:45,588
with Daniela's allegations ourselves.

276
00:16:46,256 --> 00:16:48,675
So that means no US trip.

277
00:16:48,758 --> 00:16:50,802
You and Gem are not going anywhere.

278
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:52,721
At least, not for now.

279
00:16:52,804 --> 00:16:54,097
Ace stays.

280
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,807
We need you here, son.

281
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:58,893
Your mere presence
stabilizes our partners.

282
00:16:58,977 --> 00:17:00,061
You know that!

283
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:06,067
Katarina, you handle media
and legal coordination.

284
00:17:06,151 --> 00:17:07,527
All right.

285
00:17:17,746 --> 00:17:19,706
Chaos is opportunity, love.

286
00:17:19,789 --> 00:17:22,584
Dad allowed me to handle
everything about our business.

287
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,419
So I'm going to be very busy.

288
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:26,421
That's why we won't
be going to the US for now.

289
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:33,553
I... I see, love.

290
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:37,640
Well, I can go there by myself first.

291
00:17:38,808 --> 00:17:40,018
I'll go ahead.

292
00:17:42,604 --> 00:17:44,189
Are you making your own decision?

293
00:17:44,731 --> 00:17:46,441
I just thought about it. I mean...

294
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:48,818
we've been planning
for this trip for so long,

295
00:17:48,902 --> 00:17:51,029
and I've been anticipating our flight.

296
00:17:51,112 --> 00:17:54,449
And if you can't make it,
I was thinking, I'll just go ahead.

297
00:17:55,992 --> 00:17:57,202
Are you disrespecting me?

298
00:18:00,205 --> 00:18:01,581
Answer me!

299
00:18:02,207 --> 00:18:03,666
Of course not, love.

300
00:18:05,293 --> 00:18:06,544
I was just surprised.

301
00:18:16,221 --> 00:18:17,514
I understand.

302
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:20,183
I won't go.

303
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:26,731
Is there a problem?

304
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:30,860
You look like
you have something to say.

305
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:33,363
Should you have an opinion on anything?

306
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:36,699
No, sir.

307
00:18:38,076 --> 00:18:39,494
You can have an opinion.

308
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:43,331
But if I don't ask for it, don't give it.

309
00:18:43,414 --> 00:18:44,624
Did I make myself clear?

310
00:18:47,502 --> 00:18:48,419
Yes, sir.

311
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:56,886
- Hey!
- Hey.

312
00:18:57,387 --> 00:18:58,304
Uh...

313
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:00,890
Good afternoon, ma'am.

314
00:19:00,974 --> 00:19:02,851
- How are you?
- I'm okay.

315
00:19:04,185 --> 00:19:07,355
I heard about the allegations...

316
00:19:07,438 --> 00:19:08,690
about your family.

317
00:19:08,773 --> 00:19:10,775
I'm sure a lot of people
have read about it.

318
00:19:11,276 --> 00:19:12,318
Are they true?

319
00:19:12,402 --> 00:19:14,779
Well, Mommy said they aren't.

320
00:19:14,863 --> 00:19:16,197
Do you believe her?

321
00:19:16,281 --> 00:19:18,366
I don't have a choice. Family.

322
00:19:18,449 --> 00:19:20,493
Besides, there is no proof.

323
00:19:20,577 --> 00:19:24,539
It's wrong to believe
that doesn't have any proof, right?

324
00:19:27,709 --> 00:19:29,919
Anything to eat
with your Spanish latte?

325
00:19:30,003 --> 00:19:31,796
Nothing, just this.

326
00:19:32,297 --> 00:19:33,339
Okay, ma'am.

327
00:19:34,132 --> 00:19:35,341
Thank you.

328
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:51,274
Don't worry.

329
00:19:51,858 --> 00:19:53,151
The truth will come out soon.

330
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:55,904
Why would those people
try to go against you...

331
00:19:56,779 --> 00:19:58,489
the ones who actually know the law?

332
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:01,451
What about the phone call
she's talking about?

333
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:02,702
According to the affidavit,

334
00:20:02,785 --> 00:20:05,580
it is not true that she asked me
to speak with you.

335
00:20:05,663 --> 00:20:08,291
There are no records
from the telecommunications companies.

336
00:20:12,962 --> 00:20:14,005
Thank you.

337
00:20:19,469 --> 00:20:20,386
Colonel.

338
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:24,015
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

339
00:20:24,098 --> 00:20:25,141
That's enough!

340
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:26,434
It's over, isn't it?

341
00:20:26,517 --> 00:20:28,186
I'm not here to make a scene.

342
00:20:28,269 --> 00:20:29,604
But if you know something...

343
00:20:30,939 --> 00:20:32,023
you should speak up.

344
00:20:32,106 --> 00:20:34,692
The Veronas have too many victims already.

345
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:36,152
Now is the time to speak up...

346
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:37,654
before they add more people
to their list of victims.

347
00:20:39,072 --> 00:20:40,198
I don't know anything.

348
00:20:41,324 --> 00:20:42,408
Okay.

349
00:20:42,492 --> 00:20:43,576
Okay, that's enough!

350
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:45,578
Sir.

351
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:57,382
I trust you to handle that reporter.

352
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,677
Yes, Pa.
I know what you mean.

353
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:05,682
I'll file a lawsuit against him, right?

354
00:21:05,765 --> 00:21:06,891
Yes.

355
00:21:07,809 --> 00:21:09,018
A restraining order.

356
00:21:21,072 --> 00:21:22,323
<i>The sheikh gave this to me.</i>

357
00:21:22,407 --> 00:21:25,076
<i>He said it's Moroccan amethyst.</i>

358
00:21:25,159 --> 00:21:27,078
<i>It's a symbol of honor...</i>

359
00:21:27,996 --> 00:21:29,205
<i>truth...</i>

360
00:21:30,540 --> 00:21:31,624
<i>and love.</i>

361
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:44,012
This is not meant for me.

362
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:50,476
<i>Hey, this is Jepoy.</i>

363
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:52,353
I'm back in the Philippines now.

364
00:21:52,437 --> 00:21:54,731
Oh, Jepoy. How are you?
What's the problem?

365
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:56,399
My father had an emergency.

366
00:21:56,941 --> 00:21:57,900
He had a stroke.

367
00:21:57,984 --> 00:22:01,070
I thought he was dying,
so I came home immediately.

368
00:22:01,696 --> 00:22:04,615
I'm sorry to hear that, Jepoy.
How is he doing now?

369
00:22:04,699 --> 00:22:06,909
<i>By God's grace, he's still alive.</i>

370
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:08,453
But he's bedridden now.

371
00:22:08,536 --> 00:22:11,164
Where's the hospital?
I plan to make a visit.

372
00:22:11,247 --> 00:22:12,707
<i>Thank you.</i>

373
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:14,417
<i>We're here in Manila.</i>

374
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,794
But I'm sorry, Teo.

375
00:22:18,087 --> 00:22:19,839
It's just that
I'm in a tight spot right now.

376
00:22:19,922 --> 00:22:21,924
<i>My father's hospital bill</i>
<i>is too expensive.</i>

377
00:22:22,008 --> 00:22:23,634
<i>I've used up all of my savings.</i>

378
00:22:23,718 --> 00:22:25,720
Teo, do you have a job
you can refer me to?

379
00:22:25,803 --> 00:22:26,888
Jepoy...

380
00:22:27,972 --> 00:22:29,182
I understand.

381
00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:32,393
But I have no jobs to refer to you.

382
00:22:33,144 --> 00:22:35,271
<i>I can't have you working where I work.</i>

383
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:36,981
You know my situation, don't you?

384
00:22:37,065 --> 00:22:38,775
<i>But don't worry, I'll help you.</i>

385
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:40,109
Just wait a little bit.

386
00:22:40,193 --> 00:22:43,696
Thank you, Teo. I'll take any job.

387
00:22:44,238 --> 00:22:46,991
Take care. I'll pray for your father.

388
00:22:47,075 --> 00:22:49,452
Thank you, Teo. You take care as well.

389
00:22:53,706 --> 00:22:56,375
Hey! You're already burning
the clothes you're ironing.

390
00:22:56,459 --> 00:22:57,877
But is it true?

391
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,128
What are you even watching?

392
00:22:59,212 --> 00:23:00,588
That thing about Daniela?

393
00:23:00,671 --> 00:23:02,715
The allegations she made
in her press conference

394
00:23:02,799 --> 00:23:05,051
were really serious.

395
00:23:05,134 --> 00:23:07,970
That's why she went into hiding.

396
00:23:08,054 --> 00:23:09,514
I think...

397
00:23:09,597 --> 00:23:11,557
the Veronas will have her killed.

398
00:23:11,641 --> 00:23:13,476
- Mabel!
- What?

399
00:23:16,229 --> 00:23:18,022
We're the only people here anyway.

400
00:23:18,731 --> 00:23:20,775
Hey, Teo. Don't tell anyone about this.

401
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:23,486
Are you serious about that?
They're our employers.

402
00:23:23,569 --> 00:23:25,613
And if it's true, why isn't
anybody reporting it?

403
00:23:25,696 --> 00:23:29,033
Teo, that's why you
shouldn't go against the Veronas.

404
00:23:29,117 --> 00:23:31,077
Or else you'll just be another headline.

405
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,412
Ma'am! You have no proof.

406
00:23:35,081 --> 00:23:36,707
Well, maybe Teo has.

407
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:39,168
You're always with Sir Ace, aren't you?

408
00:23:39,669 --> 00:23:42,755
Do you really know nothing?
Have you seen anything?

409
00:23:42,839 --> 00:23:45,550
Do you remember
Sir Ace's former driver?

410
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:49,387
He suddenly went missing
after allegedly stealing something?

411
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:51,848
We never heard about him ever again.

412
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:55,017
You should keep quiet now.

413
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:56,978
My gosh.

414
00:23:57,687 --> 00:23:59,021
Maybe he just resigned.

415
00:23:59,105 --> 00:24:01,274
The Veronas would never
let anything just slide.

416
00:24:01,357 --> 00:24:04,485
If you make up some rumors
about them, they'll fight back.

417
00:24:04,569 --> 00:24:07,905
They'll make you pay
even for the slightest offense.

418
00:24:07,989 --> 00:24:09,532
So both of you...

419
00:24:09,615 --> 00:24:11,576
- Mabel?
- What?

420
00:24:11,659 --> 00:24:13,619
You too, Teo, you guys better behave.

421
00:24:22,128 --> 00:24:25,506
Eric, track down where
Daniela's family is staying.

422
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:27,383
Sir, take it easy.

423
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:31,262
Don't give them a reason
to get you even more involved.

424
00:24:33,848 --> 00:24:36,851
Remember, you're already on their radar.

425
00:24:36,934 --> 00:24:38,769
One wrong move, and it's over.

426
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:40,438
You don't get it.

427
00:24:41,355 --> 00:24:42,398
Papa finally trusted me

428
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:44,734
to be part of a new group
in the family business.

429
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:47,737
I don't want the plan
to fall through because of Ordoñez.

430
00:24:49,238 --> 00:24:50,865
I need you
to do something for me.

431
00:24:58,414 --> 00:25:00,374
- Sir.
- Have you been there all along?

432
00:25:00,458 --> 00:25:01,459
No, sir.

433
00:25:02,335 --> 00:25:05,254
- Are you lying to me?
- No, sir. I just arrived.

434
00:25:05,338 --> 00:25:07,882
You've heard things
you were never meant to hear.

435
00:25:07,965 --> 00:25:10,009
I didn't hear anything, sir.

436
00:25:20,228 --> 00:25:21,520
- You may leave.
- Oh.

437
00:25:22,146 --> 00:25:23,356
Sir.

438
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:29,695
It's not the end
of the world, Divino.

439
00:25:34,742 --> 00:25:37,870
My family will be destroyed
if this comes out.

440
00:25:39,247 --> 00:25:41,874
I cannot let Katarina and Ace down.

441
00:25:41,958 --> 00:25:44,877
You aren't listed
as one of the agency's incorporators.

442
00:25:44,961 --> 00:25:46,420
You're clean.

443
00:25:46,504 --> 00:25:48,214
Are you sure?

444
00:25:48,297 --> 00:25:51,133
Well, if they're going to go
after someone, it won't be you.

445
00:25:53,594 --> 00:25:55,096
I'll take care of it.

446
00:25:55,179 --> 00:25:58,182
They won't find anything
that would lead back to you.

447
00:25:58,266 --> 00:25:59,809
And if there are loopholes,

448
00:25:59,892 --> 00:26:02,311
you can get away with it.
You have your ways.

449
00:26:25,126 --> 00:26:26,877
Ah, okay. I'm glad.

450
00:26:26,961 --> 00:26:30,131
Thank you, too.
Let's just adjust the schedule.

451
00:26:35,469 --> 00:26:37,930
- Just inform Divino.
- Attorney.

452
00:26:38,014 --> 00:26:39,265
Ah, I'm Mateo Crisanto.

453
00:26:39,348 --> 00:26:43,060
You helped me once
when I was imprisoned in Morocco.

454
00:26:43,144 --> 00:26:46,439
- I just want to say thank you.
- Ah, I see, yes.

455
00:26:46,522 --> 00:26:50,234
Recently, someone asked me
the same question.

456
00:26:50,818 --> 00:26:53,321
Anyway, I'm glad
things worked out for you.

457
00:26:53,404 --> 00:26:54,822
Thank you again.

458
00:26:54,905 --> 00:26:56,699
- Okay, good luck, Mateo.
- Thank you.

459
00:26:57,908 --> 00:26:59,118
Attorney.

460
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:03,039
I also want to thank whoever
requested my pardon from you.

461
00:27:03,122 --> 00:27:05,124
That I cannot reveal.

462
00:27:05,875 --> 00:27:07,835
It turns out
you really do listen to the pleas

463
00:27:07,918 --> 00:27:10,004
of simple people like us.

464
00:27:10,087 --> 00:27:12,298
Yes. But the chances
of the pardon getting approved

465
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:13,632
are stronger if
the recommendations and requests

466
00:27:13,716 --> 00:27:15,509
come from highly credible people,

467
00:27:15,593 --> 00:27:19,805
with integrity and strong connections.

468
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:22,892
You mean rich people, am I right?

469
00:27:22,975 --> 00:27:25,644
Yes. Maybe you should ask
the Veronas about it.

470
00:27:25,728 --> 00:27:28,481
Veronas? They were
the ones who bailed me out?

471
00:27:28,564 --> 00:27:31,192
What's important is that you're free.

472
00:27:31,275 --> 00:27:33,778
So just be kind, okay?

473
00:27:34,278 --> 00:27:36,447
- Good luck, Mateo.
- Thank you, Attorney.

474
00:27:54,507 --> 00:27:57,468
You invited me out of nowhere.
Luckily, I'm on break.

475
00:27:58,511 --> 00:28:00,137
You didn't bail me out.

476
00:28:00,930 --> 00:28:02,807
- Huh?
- You heard me.

477
00:28:04,934 --> 00:28:06,227
It was me!

478
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:11,732
I wrote to the ambassadors,
legal attachés, and diplomats!

479
00:28:11,816 --> 00:28:14,777
I coordinated with OFW Groups in Morocco.

480
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:16,904
I even wrote to the president!

481
00:28:16,987 --> 00:28:18,280
Keep your voice down.

482
00:28:18,364 --> 00:28:19,407
Did you hear back from them?

483
00:28:19,490 --> 00:28:20,783
No.

484
00:28:21,617 --> 00:28:23,994
Who would put all the effort
into getting you released?

485
00:28:24,078 --> 00:28:26,080
Only me! I'm the only person you've got.

486
00:28:26,163 --> 00:28:27,915
That's not confirmed.

487
00:28:27,998 --> 00:28:29,834
According to the attorney,
only those in power

488
00:28:29,917 --> 00:28:32,294
are authorized to make
such a significant request.

489
00:28:32,378 --> 00:28:33,963
I'm sorry, then.

490
00:28:34,046 --> 00:28:35,297
I'm sorry,

491
00:28:35,381 --> 00:28:37,633
I wasn't an influential person
they'd actually listen to.

492
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,136
But at least I was able to make an effort.

493
00:28:40,678 --> 00:28:42,346
Where did this come from?

494
00:28:42,430 --> 00:28:45,975
You're already free,
why are you still so curious?

495
00:28:49,562 --> 00:28:51,897
Whether I bailed you out or not,
the bottom line is,

496
00:28:51,981 --> 00:28:53,190
I didn't lie to you.

497
00:28:54,817 --> 00:28:58,028
Because, besides my effort
and the prayers in my heart,

498
00:28:58,112 --> 00:29:00,823
I've asked for nothing else
but for you to be set free.

499
00:29:00,906 --> 00:29:04,869
If someone else really did find
a way, then fine, thank them.

500
00:29:13,794 --> 00:29:15,963
You've been texting me nonstop
since last night.

501
00:29:16,046 --> 00:29:17,548
What is it about?

502
00:29:19,383 --> 00:29:21,385
I'm sorry to bother you last night.

503
00:29:23,429 --> 00:29:24,972
I just can't put my mind at ease.

504
00:29:26,265 --> 00:29:30,186
When you jumped
from that tower in Morocco...

505
00:29:31,896 --> 00:29:33,022
when you left me...

506
00:29:34,398 --> 00:29:36,192
what happened to you?

507
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:39,612
I had to wait for a long time.

508
00:29:41,864 --> 00:29:44,450
Because I knew that
the authorities were waiting for me.

509
00:29:54,835 --> 00:29:57,671
After that, my two friends and I
talked about...

510
00:29:58,297 --> 00:29:59,798
meeting at the Ruins.

511
00:30:05,221 --> 00:30:07,389
<i>But I only saw Diane.</i>

512
00:30:09,475 --> 00:30:10,434
<i>She was dead.</i>

513
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:13,103
<i>I was too late.</i>

514
00:30:14,188 --> 00:30:17,024
<i>Even if I wanted her to live,</i>
<i>I couldn't do anything.</i>

515
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:31,539
I'm sorry.

516
00:30:46,762 --> 00:30:49,348
<i>I left my fake passports with her</i>

517
00:30:50,516 --> 00:30:52,184
<i>to confuse the investigation.</i>

518
00:30:53,352 --> 00:30:56,063
<i>And to stop the police</i>
<i>from searching for me.</i>

519
00:30:57,481 --> 00:31:00,943
<i>Diane's face was unrecognizable</i>
<i>when they recovered her body.</i>

520
00:31:01,652 --> 00:31:02,945
<i>She was bloated.</i>

521
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:06,156
<i>No one could identify</i>
<i>that the body wasn't mine.</i>

522
00:31:07,741 --> 00:31:10,661
<i>Because of the passport</i>
<i>I planted on Diane's body,</i>

523
00:31:12,037 --> 00:31:13,706
<i>the investigation was closed.</i>

524
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,293
<i>Yana Kassir was dead.</i>

525
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:23,215
I lost so many things that day.

526
00:31:25,175 --> 00:31:27,469
I lost so many important people.

527
00:31:29,054 --> 00:31:31,724
I also lost my life and my freedom.

528
00:31:31,807 --> 00:31:34,685
I didn't know that
I would live to see this day.

529
00:31:35,978 --> 00:31:37,521
I went to jail,

530
00:31:37,605 --> 00:31:39,523
and I got released because of you.

531
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,110
It's so deep... so dark...

532
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:45,779
everything that happened
to us was so painful

533
00:31:47,656 --> 00:31:48,949
But it's all right.

534
00:31:49,742 --> 00:31:51,035
We'll call it even.

535
00:31:52,745 --> 00:31:54,079
Good.

536
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:57,499
Then everything's settled.

537
00:31:58,042 --> 00:31:59,293
Teo, I really hope...

538
00:32:00,294 --> 00:32:02,129
you don't ruin your life anymore

539
00:32:03,005 --> 00:32:04,465
now that you're free.

540
00:32:04,548 --> 00:32:06,467
Like you're doing now?

541
00:32:11,138 --> 00:32:12,473
You're not happy.

542
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,145
Happiness is overrated.

543
00:32:18,228 --> 00:32:20,356
Is that why
you're putting up with him?

544
00:32:20,439 --> 00:32:22,149
Ace is my husband.

545
00:32:23,025 --> 00:32:24,360
It's your relationship.

546
00:32:25,694 --> 00:32:28,197
Thanks again. I'm free because of you.

547
00:32:29,531 --> 00:32:30,658
I hope you will be free, too.

548
00:32:42,586 --> 00:32:44,296
Here.

549
00:32:44,380 --> 00:32:45,631
It's not for me.

550
00:32:48,133 --> 00:32:49,551
But I wanted to give this to you.

551
00:32:49,635 --> 00:32:51,095
I don't deserve that.

552
00:32:52,930 --> 00:32:55,516
Gem, you gave me the freedom I wanted.

553
00:32:56,433 --> 00:32:58,435
I did something much worse.

554
00:32:58,519 --> 00:33:00,270
I ruined your life.

555
00:33:00,854 --> 00:33:03,148
That's enough.

556
00:33:18,247 --> 00:33:19,206
Well?

557
00:33:19,289 --> 00:33:21,291
Have you found a passport guy?

558
00:33:22,209 --> 00:33:23,544
I need about five.

559
00:33:23,627 --> 00:33:26,380
<i>Five? For five different countries?</i>

560
00:33:26,463 --> 00:33:27,965
I don't plan on coming back.

561
00:33:28,590 --> 00:33:30,467
<i>When are you leaving?</i>

562
00:33:30,551 --> 00:33:32,094
I'll leave alone.

563
00:33:32,177 --> 00:33:33,137
<i>Did Ace agree to that?</i>

564
00:33:33,220 --> 00:33:34,346
I don't care if he doesn't agree.

565
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:36,265
Whatever happens,
I'm going through with the plan.

566
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:39,184
<i>Okay. I'll take care of it.</i>

567
00:33:39,685 --> 00:33:40,853
<i>Are you going to send money?</i>

568
00:33:41,603 --> 00:33:44,273
Ace can monitor online transactions.

569
00:33:45,566 --> 00:33:46,734
I'll find another way.

570
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:49,361
Thank you, Gimo.

571
00:34:18,682 --> 00:34:19,975
What a day!

572
00:34:24,897 --> 00:34:25,731
Love!

573
00:34:27,816 --> 00:34:29,109
What are you doing, love?

574
00:34:29,193 --> 00:34:31,612
I was just looking
for a pendant, and you know,

575
00:34:31,695 --> 00:34:33,197
one thing led to another.

576
00:34:33,947 --> 00:34:34,865
Hey...

577
00:34:38,494 --> 00:34:40,329
This was my anniversary gift for you.

578
00:34:40,412 --> 00:34:41,246
Switzerland.

579
00:34:41,330 --> 00:34:43,874
That I haven't even used.

580
00:34:44,708 --> 00:34:47,377
Love,
I was thinking of, you know...

581
00:34:48,545 --> 00:34:50,005
putting it somewhere safe.

582
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:52,674
Somewhere it won't wear out
or get buried in clutter.

583
00:34:52,758 --> 00:34:54,384
I was thinking of, maybe,
like a vault.

584
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:56,512
You already have a vault.

585
00:34:56,595 --> 00:34:58,806
I know, love.

586
00:34:59,515 --> 00:35:00,641
But you know, like,

587
00:35:01,225 --> 00:35:02,810
like a fake vault.

588
00:35:03,852 --> 00:35:07,064
A much bigger, much safer...

589
00:35:08,690 --> 00:35:09,608
vault.

590
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:13,779
You want more?

591
00:35:18,367 --> 00:35:19,493
What do you want?

592
00:35:20,327 --> 00:35:21,411
A new watch?

593
00:35:23,121 --> 00:35:25,165
- Diamond necklace?
- A property.

594
00:35:29,294 --> 00:35:30,170
Wow.

595
00:35:31,088 --> 00:35:32,881
Love, I know.

596
00:35:32,965 --> 00:35:34,466
I know. Wow, right?

597
00:35:34,550 --> 00:35:36,593
But, like, I was thinking, love,
you know...

598
00:35:37,719 --> 00:35:39,555
I thought about this for a long time.

599
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:43,684
I saw a property that's
so beautiful with so much potential.

600
00:35:43,767 --> 00:35:45,227
I wanna make it into a resort.

601
00:35:45,894 --> 00:35:47,396
It's 23 million.

602
00:35:48,522 --> 00:35:51,358
And since
we're not going to the US,

603
00:35:51,441 --> 00:35:53,277
might as well build us a home here.

604
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:56,488
You know, like, somewhere we could run to,

605
00:35:56,572 --> 00:35:58,782
somewhere we can hide and just feel safe.

606
00:35:59,324 --> 00:36:00,826
Just the two of us.

607
00:36:03,453 --> 00:36:05,831
Me, a sanctuary.

608
00:36:15,966 --> 00:36:17,759
We have savings in our joint account.

609
00:36:18,552 --> 00:36:20,345
Just tell me when to pay.

610
00:36:21,805 --> 00:36:23,015
Mm.

611
00:36:23,098 --> 00:36:24,600
That's why I love you so much.

612
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:26,602
You really know how to spoil me.

613
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:27,728
I love you, too.

614
00:36:33,901 --> 00:36:35,444
You just got here.

615
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:36,695
You need to shower.

616
00:36:37,487 --> 00:36:38,572
Oh, yeah.

617
00:36:38,655 --> 00:36:40,073
I gotta shower. Long day.

618
00:36:40,157 --> 00:36:41,325
Yeah.

619
00:36:45,621 --> 00:36:46,663
I'll be right back.

620
00:36:46,747 --> 00:36:47,998
I'm waiting for you.

621
00:36:57,674 --> 00:36:59,468
I knew this would happen.

622
00:36:59,551 --> 00:37:02,179
If you have any feelings
for the Gem woman,

623
00:37:02,971 --> 00:37:04,306
it's gonna be complicated.

624
00:37:04,389 --> 00:37:07,017
It's going nowhere, Pa. I'm done with it.

625
00:37:07,100 --> 00:37:08,226
Then, that's good.

626
00:37:10,479 --> 00:37:12,022
If I were you,

627
00:37:12,105 --> 00:37:15,442
I'd just treat her like an ex-girlfriend.

628
00:37:15,525 --> 00:37:18,320
She was the reason you got jailed,

629
00:37:18,403 --> 00:37:21,281
and she was the reason that you went free.

630
00:37:21,365 --> 00:37:22,658
That's the thing, Papa.

631
00:37:23,158 --> 00:37:24,952
We're living our own lives now.

632
00:37:25,035 --> 00:37:27,287
Yeah! That's good!

633
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:31,625
Just focus on your job now, all right?

634
00:37:33,543 --> 00:37:35,629
Come on, let's dig in
on that fried chicken.

635
00:37:35,712 --> 00:37:37,047
- Issay!
- Yes?

636
00:37:37,130 --> 00:37:39,508
Come on. Your brother
brought home fried chicken.

637
00:37:39,591 --> 00:37:40,676
Just a second, Pa.

638
00:37:41,927 --> 00:37:43,095
Who are you talking to?

639
00:37:43,178 --> 00:37:45,806
It's Jenny, the daughter
of that woman in the news,

640
00:37:45,889 --> 00:37:47,933
Daniela Ordoñez.

641
00:37:48,016 --> 00:37:50,894
We were classmates.
We're just chatting.

642
00:37:50,978 --> 00:37:52,354
How are they doing?

643
00:37:52,437 --> 00:37:54,439
I feel bad for Jenny.

644
00:37:54,523 --> 00:37:57,776
She still hasn't seen her mother.

645
00:37:57,859 --> 00:38:00,904
Plus, the Veronas
filed a case against them.

646
00:38:00,988 --> 00:38:03,657
So now they're being harassed
on social media.

647
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:09,287
Also, her aunt lost her job
because she defied the Veronas.

648
00:38:09,371 --> 00:38:12,541
They're asking for support now.

649
00:38:13,542 --> 00:38:15,544
That's too bad, huh?

650
00:38:16,044 --> 00:38:17,462
Come on, let's eat.

651
00:38:17,546 --> 00:38:18,797
- Don't worry about it.
- Yes, Pa.

652
00:38:19,339 --> 00:38:20,966
Just go to the kitchen.

653
00:38:26,263 --> 00:38:27,848
You're awfully quiet today.

654
00:38:28,807 --> 00:38:32,019
Are you still upset that
you couldn't go on your US trip?

655
00:38:32,102 --> 00:38:33,562
Of course not, Mama.

656
00:38:34,521 --> 00:38:36,440
We might not be able to go now,

657
00:38:36,523 --> 00:38:38,984
but we'll definitely get there.

658
00:38:40,235 --> 00:38:42,446
Excuse me.
I'll prepare for my meeting.

659
00:38:43,113 --> 00:38:45,949
- With Mrs. Lardizabal?
- Yes.

660
00:38:46,491 --> 00:38:49,703
Oh. I wanted to be in that meeting too,

661
00:38:49,786 --> 00:38:52,706
except that I do have another meeting.

662
00:38:52,789 --> 00:38:53,749
That's too bad.

663
00:38:54,458 --> 00:38:56,418
- Larajean?
- Yes, ma'am?

664
00:38:57,461 --> 00:38:59,463
Go with Gem to her meeting.

665
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:02,215
Assist her.

666
00:39:03,508 --> 00:39:04,551
And Gem,

667
00:39:05,761 --> 00:39:06,887
teach her.

668
00:39:09,639 --> 00:39:12,934
Ma'am Gem, it would be an honor.

669
00:39:13,018 --> 00:39:14,895
I can learn a lot from you.

670
00:39:14,978 --> 00:39:16,396
Oh, and Gem.

671
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:19,107
If you're going on
that US trip with Ace,

672
00:39:19,941 --> 00:39:21,443
we're gonna have to replace you.

673
00:39:22,486 --> 00:39:23,612
Noted, Mama.

674
00:39:28,992 --> 00:39:31,703
Before you face a client,
you need to do some research.

675
00:39:31,787 --> 00:39:32,913
Study them.

676
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:35,373
What kind of jewelry do they want?

677
00:39:35,916 --> 00:39:37,709
What kind of stones
she likes.

678
00:39:38,877 --> 00:39:40,587
Does she like diamonds?

679
00:39:41,505 --> 00:39:42,839
Or does she like gold?

680
00:39:44,132 --> 00:39:46,593
Um, she likes diamonds, ma'am.

681
00:39:46,676 --> 00:39:49,262
Know her birthday, too.

682
00:39:49,346 --> 00:39:51,473
- Yes, ma'am.
- Find out her birthstone.

683
00:39:53,308 --> 00:39:55,102
Emerald, ma'am.

684
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:59,815
I hope it's that easy
to study a person, too.

685
00:40:01,274 --> 00:40:03,068
Just like jewelry.

686
00:40:04,778 --> 00:40:05,737
Did you know?

687
00:40:05,821 --> 00:40:08,990
Teo thought you were a girl
he knew back in Marrakech.

688
00:40:09,074 --> 00:40:10,492
I know.

689
00:40:10,575 --> 00:40:12,994
When we first met,
he called me by a different name.

690
00:40:13,078 --> 00:40:14,037
Yana.

691
00:40:14,955 --> 00:40:16,081
Yana Kassir.

692
00:40:18,250 --> 00:40:19,376
I'm thirsty.

693
00:40:19,459 --> 00:40:20,585
Can you get me water?

694
00:40:21,545 --> 00:40:22,921
Yes, ma'am.

695
00:40:26,550 --> 00:40:29,761
I just heard about that, by the way.

696
00:40:32,848 --> 00:40:34,432
Did you know?

697
00:40:35,225 --> 00:40:37,144
Teo and I have known
each other for a long time.

698
00:40:38,645 --> 00:40:39,938
In fact...

699
00:40:41,857 --> 00:40:42,941
I'm his ex.

700
00:40:43,024 --> 00:40:44,192
Hmm.

701
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:48,864
I see.

702
00:40:52,742 --> 00:40:55,745
But that's all in the past, ma'am.

703
00:40:59,457 --> 00:41:02,210
Who are we trying to fool
when we say that?

704
00:41:02,294 --> 00:41:04,212
Everyone we used to date

705
00:41:04,296 --> 00:41:08,091
never really leaves our memory.

706
00:41:09,050 --> 00:41:11,428
And you know what?
Teo is a bit hot-headed,

707
00:41:11,511 --> 00:41:14,806
but he was so sweet to me.

708
00:41:14,890 --> 00:41:17,350
He used to spoil me a lot.

709
00:41:17,434 --> 00:41:19,603
He was protective,
always looking out for me.

710
00:41:19,686 --> 00:41:22,063
He could even beat
someone up for me, ma'am.

711
00:41:22,147 --> 00:41:25,942
Then I went to Marrakech to work.

712
00:41:26,026 --> 00:41:27,777
But he couldn't stay away.

713
00:41:27,861 --> 00:41:29,446
He followed me there.

714
00:41:29,529 --> 00:41:31,489
So why did you break up?

715
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:34,701
It didn't work out.

716
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:38,413
I fell for someone else,
and he couldn't accept it.

717
00:41:38,496 --> 00:41:41,499
But he still followed me to Marrakech

718
00:41:41,583 --> 00:41:44,419
until we both came back here
to the Philippines.

719
00:41:57,182 --> 00:41:58,183
Sir?

720
00:41:58,266 --> 00:42:00,185
Attorney Verona! Sir! Sir!

721
00:42:00,268 --> 00:42:02,854
Sir, why did you file a petition

722
00:42:02,938 --> 00:42:05,565
to remove my sister
from witness protection?

723
00:42:05,649 --> 00:42:07,859
She's telling the truth.

724
00:42:07,943 --> 00:42:09,903
Ma'am,
you don't have any proof.

725
00:42:09,986 --> 00:42:10,862
- What?
- Besides,

726
00:42:10,946 --> 00:42:12,864
Daniela is not a credible witness.

727
00:42:12,948 --> 00:42:14,324
Her story falls apart under scrutiny.

728
00:42:14,407 --> 00:42:16,743
No physical evidence, no corroboration.

729
00:42:17,244 --> 00:42:19,037
She's simply not witness material.

730
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,872
Sir, just say it.

731
00:42:20,956 --> 00:42:24,709
You're using your power
to crush your enemies!

732
00:42:24,793 --> 00:42:26,670
And then you hide your own dirt.

733
00:42:26,753 --> 00:42:30,257
While people like us,
our lives are already ruined!

734
00:42:30,340 --> 00:42:32,050
Sir, please help us!

735
00:42:32,133 --> 00:42:33,760
I'm sorry, I can't help you.

736
00:42:33,843 --> 00:42:35,720
- I have a hearing to attend.
- Sir!

737
00:42:35,804 --> 00:42:37,055
Attorney!

738
00:42:37,138 --> 00:42:38,848
Sir, she's my sister!

739
00:42:38,932 --> 00:42:40,558
Please help us!

740
00:42:40,642 --> 00:42:43,270
Sir, have mercy on my sister!

741
00:42:43,353 --> 00:42:44,813
She's a human being, sir!

742
00:43:03,123 --> 00:43:04,165
Sir.

743
00:43:24,728 --> 00:43:26,646
I left my coat and some files
at the office.

744
00:43:26,730 --> 00:43:27,981
- Can you get it?
- Yes, sir.

745
00:43:28,064 --> 00:43:29,691
Ace! Ace.

746
00:43:30,317 --> 00:43:31,818
- Yes?
- I think you should hear this.

747
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:35,905
I just found out Gem
deposited jewelry in the vault.

748
00:43:36,656 --> 00:43:40,368
The bank manager is my friend.
He texted me himself.

749
00:43:41,328 --> 00:43:42,662
But I was just wondering.

750
00:43:43,413 --> 00:43:44,748
Did you give her all that?

751
00:43:46,166 --> 00:43:48,001
Or did she earn all of those?

752
00:43:50,962 --> 00:43:53,548
I mean, whichever it is,
it's quite impressive.

753
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:58,511
I didn't realize Gem
could live so lavishly

754
00:43:58,595 --> 00:44:02,223
without you, Ace.

755
00:44:21,576 --> 00:44:22,577
Sir.

756
00:44:23,328 --> 00:44:24,245
Teo.

757
00:44:25,413 --> 00:44:26,539
What are you doing here?

758
00:44:27,749 --> 00:44:29,626
I was just going to get Sir Ace's things.

759
00:44:29,709 --> 00:44:30,877
He said he left them here.

760
00:44:32,212 --> 00:44:33,213
Okay.

761
00:44:40,136 --> 00:44:41,388
Here.

762
00:44:41,471 --> 00:44:42,555
Thank you, sir.

763
00:44:42,639 --> 00:44:43,681
Do you need anything else?

764
00:44:43,765 --> 00:44:45,975
I'll go ahead, sir. Thank you.

765
00:46:28,203 --> 00:46:29,162
Son.

766
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:31,748
We already talked about this.

767
00:46:33,541 --> 00:46:37,128
Miss Lydia's sister said that
everything Daniela said is true.

768
00:46:37,754 --> 00:46:39,214
I've already connected everything

769
00:46:39,297 --> 00:46:41,966
based on what I've noticed
about the Veronas.

770
00:46:42,050 --> 00:46:43,676
Like earlier,

771
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:45,553
I found out she's no longer
in witness protection.

772
00:46:45,637 --> 00:46:48,348
I suspect the Veronas are behind that.

773
00:46:48,431 --> 00:46:50,558
Is this about Daniela or about Gem?

774
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:53,478
She doesn't want me
to disrupt her life anymore.

775
00:46:53,561 --> 00:46:55,647
Her life is actually better.

776
00:46:57,273 --> 00:47:00,151
But what if everything we've heard
about the Veronas is true?

777
00:47:00,902 --> 00:47:02,195
And they have Gem.

778
00:47:02,278 --> 00:47:03,446
Son...

779
00:47:03,530 --> 00:47:05,031
I just want to be fair, Pa.

780
00:47:05,949 --> 00:47:08,868
As long as someone is being oppressed,
it's not fair.

781
00:47:08,952 --> 00:47:12,288
Son, be fair to yourself as well.

782
00:47:12,372 --> 00:47:15,625
Don't always choose others over yourself.

783
00:47:29,681 --> 00:47:30,682
Judge.

784
00:47:34,936 --> 00:47:36,229
- Steven.
- Sir?

785
00:47:36,312 --> 00:47:38,106
Did the mechanic come earlier?

786
00:47:38,189 --> 00:47:39,274
No, sir.

787
00:47:39,357 --> 00:47:41,025
I called him, but he didn't answer.

788
00:47:41,109 --> 00:47:43,069
Don't call him again.

789
00:47:43,152 --> 00:47:45,613
Judge, what if I just bring
the car to the dealership?

790
00:47:45,697 --> 00:47:47,156
I don't trust them.

791
00:47:47,824 --> 00:47:49,117
You know why.

792
00:47:49,200 --> 00:47:52,245
Judge, I know another mechanic.
You might want to try him.

793
00:47:57,667 --> 00:47:58,710
Hello, sir?

794
00:47:58,793 --> 00:48:01,170
Teo, can your father work as a mechanic

795
00:48:01,254 --> 00:48:02,547
<i>at the mansion for now?</i>

796
00:48:02,630 --> 00:48:05,216
<i>You said he handles vintage cars, right?</i>

797
00:48:05,300 --> 00:48:07,760
You're already busy driving
for Sir Ace and Ma'am Gem.

798
00:48:07,844 --> 00:48:10,013
All right, sir. I'll ask my dad.

799
00:48:10,096 --> 00:48:11,806
Okay, update me.

800
00:48:14,017 --> 00:48:14,976
What is it?

801
00:48:17,270 --> 00:48:18,646
Sir Steven is asking

802
00:48:18,730 --> 00:48:20,481
if you can work as a mechanic
at the house.

803
00:48:20,565 --> 00:48:23,484
- Of course, I can.
- But no, Pa.

804
00:48:23,568 --> 00:48:24,527
Why not?

805
00:48:25,403 --> 00:48:26,988
That's extra income.

806
00:48:27,071 --> 00:48:28,948
Don't you want me to help you here?

807
00:48:29,032 --> 00:48:32,243
Pa, you'll just make things
harder for Teo.

808
00:48:32,327 --> 00:48:35,163
You can't take that risk.
Please don't be stubborn.

809
00:48:36,456 --> 00:48:38,875
I'll just find you another job, okay?

810
00:48:39,959 --> 00:48:41,544
Not with the Veronas.

811
00:48:43,421 --> 00:48:45,173
Sir Alonzo?

812
00:48:45,256 --> 00:48:46,257
Sir Alonzo!

813
00:48:46,341 --> 00:48:47,383
- Larajean!
- Larajean.

814
00:48:47,467 --> 00:48:48,843
I brought something for you.

815
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:50,428
Here.

816
00:48:50,511 --> 00:48:52,388
- That's a lot.
- Hi, Teo.

817
00:48:53,389 --> 00:48:55,350
Uh, Issay, there's milk here for you.

818
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:57,143
That's a lot. You didn't have to.

819
00:48:57,226 --> 00:48:58,436
No, no, it's nothing.

820
00:48:58,519 --> 00:49:00,730
I sold some jewelry earlier.

821
00:49:00,813 --> 00:49:03,316
I got a big commission.

822
00:49:03,399 --> 00:49:06,402
And there's more to come,
thanks to Ma'am Gem.

823
00:49:08,154 --> 00:49:10,531
- Why?
- She's training me to sell.

824
00:49:38,935 --> 00:49:42,438
The rest of the associates
want to meet with us, Earl.

825
00:49:42,522 --> 00:49:44,816
They want to know
that their interests in the business

826
00:49:44,899 --> 00:49:46,025
are still safe.

827
00:49:47,568 --> 00:49:51,906
Sir Alonzo. Good thing you made it.
Teo said you already turned this down.

828
00:49:51,989 --> 00:49:54,617
Who would ever turn down money?

829
00:49:55,451 --> 00:49:58,579
I just had to find someone
to cover for me at the car wash.

830
00:49:58,663 --> 00:50:00,123
Are you sure it won't be a problem?

831
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:04,335
Of course not!
Everything's been taken care of.

832
00:50:04,419 --> 00:50:06,379
It's too bad you missed Teo.

833
00:50:08,256 --> 00:50:09,382
- Look at this.
- What's that?

834
00:50:11,801 --> 00:50:13,553
So this is the main villa.

835
00:50:15,304 --> 00:50:16,931
It's so, so beautiful.

836
00:50:17,014 --> 00:50:20,727
Love, I'm sure this will be
a great investment.

837
00:50:20,810 --> 00:50:22,520
Not just that, wait.

838
00:50:23,521 --> 00:50:24,856
Look at the pool area.

839
00:50:24,939 --> 00:50:26,524
It's so beautiful, love.

840
00:50:26,607 --> 00:50:28,151
Yes, it is beautiful, love.

841
00:50:28,693 --> 00:50:31,571
But I want to see it
before we make an offer.

842
00:50:31,654 --> 00:50:33,114
Just to make sure
it's worth it.

843
00:50:33,197 --> 00:50:34,866
Then let's schedule a visit.

844
00:50:35,366 --> 00:50:36,909
You're always busy, love.

845
00:50:36,993 --> 00:50:39,620
I heard a lot of people
are interested in the property.

846
00:50:39,704 --> 00:50:41,998
They might beat us to it.

847
00:50:45,418 --> 00:50:46,627
Okay.

848
00:50:46,711 --> 00:50:48,212
Let's schedule a visit, all right?

849
00:50:48,963 --> 00:50:50,548
Okay!

850
00:50:50,631 --> 00:50:52,633
Okay, let me show you this.

851
00:50:52,717 --> 00:50:55,303
So, this will be our villa.

852
00:50:55,386 --> 00:50:59,015
And then this will be our kids' villa.

853
00:50:59,098 --> 00:51:01,392
- Excuse me, love, I'll just get this.
- Okay.

854
00:51:05,897 --> 00:51:06,814
Yes, Eric?

855
00:51:06,898 --> 00:51:10,151
Sir, Daniela's witness protection

856
00:51:10,860 --> 00:51:12,236
is not granted.

857
00:51:19,035 --> 00:51:20,453
- There he is!
- Here they come.

858
00:51:21,037 --> 00:51:22,747
Attorney! Attorney Verona!

859
00:51:22,830 --> 00:51:23,915
Any comments on the denial

860
00:51:23,998 --> 00:51:26,459
of the witness protection request
of Daniela Ordoñez?

861
00:51:26,542 --> 00:51:28,002
Was it really expected?

862
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:29,420
Is she really not qualified?

863
00:51:32,089 --> 00:51:33,466
I'll keep it straightforward, huh?

864
00:51:34,217 --> 00:51:35,468
She is not credible.

865
00:51:35,551 --> 00:51:38,012
We filed a petition about that,
and it was granted.

866
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:39,931
The law is always on the side
of the innocent.

867
00:51:40,014 --> 00:51:42,809
And we Veronas believe in the law.

868
00:51:42,892 --> 00:51:44,060
That'll be all for today.

869
00:51:44,143 --> 00:51:45,645
- But sir--
- That's enough.

870
00:51:45,728 --> 00:51:47,605
I said that's all for today.

871
00:51:49,649 --> 00:51:50,858
Go ahead, gentlemen.

872
00:51:55,363 --> 00:51:58,908
Eric, you know what to do with Daniela.

873
00:52:01,869 --> 00:52:03,371
Teo, I have to go somewhere.

874
00:52:03,454 --> 00:52:04,747
I'll drive myself. Go home.

875
00:52:04,831 --> 00:52:06,541
Okay, sir.

876
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:20,346
Issay, I need to talk to Jenny.

877
00:52:24,183 --> 00:52:28,396
Jenny, if you know where your mom is,
please tell me.

878
00:52:28,896 --> 00:52:30,273
Her life is in danger.

879
00:52:30,356 --> 00:52:34,193
My aunt told me you work for the Veronas.

880
00:52:34,277 --> 00:52:35,945
Why should I believe you?

881
00:52:36,028 --> 00:52:39,156
For your mom's sake, you have to trust me.

882
00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:40,616
They're going to kill her.

883
00:52:40,700 --> 00:52:43,744
I will bring her home to you, alive.

884
00:52:43,828 --> 00:52:46,497
But that'll only be possible
if you tell me where she is.

885
00:52:56,132 --> 00:52:57,466
Who are you?

886
00:52:58,050 --> 00:53:00,970
You need to leave.
There are people coming to kill you.

887
00:53:01,470 --> 00:53:02,722
Why should I believe you?

888
00:53:04,348 --> 00:53:06,392
Your daughter is friends with my sister.

889
00:53:06,475 --> 00:53:08,436
I... It's a long story.

890
00:53:10,980 --> 00:53:14,191
How can I be sure
you're not the one sent to kill me?

891
00:53:14,275 --> 00:53:15,526
You have to trust me.

892
00:53:18,237 --> 00:53:19,280
Shh!

893
00:53:22,491 --> 00:53:23,993
Over here.

894
00:53:27,163 --> 00:53:28,122
Where?

895
00:53:45,932 --> 00:53:47,016
Hey!

896
00:53:48,517 --> 00:53:49,810
Come on!

897
00:53:55,524 --> 00:53:56,943
Get out of here. I'll catch up.

898
00:54:12,959 --> 00:54:13,960
Hurry!

899
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:32,311
Who are you? Why are you helping me?

900
00:54:33,980 --> 00:54:35,439
Jenny is your daughter, right?

901
00:54:36,565 --> 00:54:38,401
I told you,

902
00:54:38,484 --> 00:54:40,945
she's friends with my sister, Issay.

903
00:54:43,114 --> 00:54:44,949
I'm also the son of Rita Crisanto.

904
00:54:45,032 --> 00:54:47,284
Do you know what happened to my mother?

905
00:54:47,368 --> 00:54:48,911
You recruited her, didn't you?

906
00:54:48,995 --> 00:54:52,081
Yes, but not in Dubai.

907
00:54:52,665 --> 00:54:55,084
We met a Filipino recruiter there

908
00:54:55,167 --> 00:54:59,046
who promised to help us get to Italy.

909
00:54:59,797 --> 00:55:01,382
We trusted them because
they were fellow Filipinos.

910
00:55:01,465 --> 00:55:03,592
They even showed credentials
to prove they were legitimate,

911
00:55:03,676 --> 00:55:05,469
but they were still frauds.

912
00:55:05,553 --> 00:55:07,430
I wound up in Zanzibar.

913
00:55:07,513 --> 00:55:10,099
I don't know where Rita ended up.

914
00:55:17,481 --> 00:55:18,524
She went to Morocco.

915
00:55:21,736 --> 00:55:23,612
I went there to look for her, but...

916
00:55:26,157 --> 00:55:27,533
She'd been dead for five years already.

917
00:55:29,785 --> 00:55:32,038
Do you know what happened to my mother?

918
00:55:32,121 --> 00:55:36,625
I don't know for sure,
but those who were brought to Morocco

919
00:55:36,709 --> 00:55:37,877
were taken to Casablanca.

920
00:55:39,587 --> 00:55:43,049
I became a domestic slave.

921
00:55:43,132 --> 00:55:44,467
It was hell!

922
00:55:45,926 --> 00:55:48,387
I was abused every day.

923
00:55:48,471 --> 00:55:49,764
Until...

924
00:55:50,431 --> 00:55:53,601
one day, I was thrown out onto the street.

925
00:55:54,268 --> 00:55:57,438
I was found by a fellow Filipino.

926
00:55:58,439 --> 00:55:59,982
Who helped me, but...

927
00:56:00,066 --> 00:56:02,610
then just took me back to the agency.

928
00:56:03,694 --> 00:56:04,987
To Al Khair?

929
00:56:05,071 --> 00:56:09,867
Yes, but the agency had
a different name back then.

930
00:56:09,950 --> 00:56:12,870
Sahara Manpower Incorporated.

931
00:56:35,684 --> 00:56:36,727
Gem!

932
00:56:37,937 --> 00:56:38,896
Gem!

933
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:44,026
Do you remember
when we were looking for my mother

934
00:56:44,110 --> 00:56:45,319
in Casablanca?

935
00:56:45,402 --> 00:56:47,613
What else do you know about her?

936
00:56:50,324 --> 00:56:52,326
Only what Mama Nadia told us.

937
00:56:55,121 --> 00:56:57,248
That she met your mother in Morocco.

938
00:56:58,207 --> 00:56:59,166
That's it.

939
00:56:59,959 --> 00:57:01,752
Maybe Miss Nadia knows more about

940
00:57:01,836 --> 00:57:04,338
how Mama got to Morocco.

941
00:57:04,421 --> 00:57:07,925
I think she was a victim
of human trafficking.

942
00:57:08,008 --> 00:57:10,010
But she couldn't tell us.

943
00:57:22,022 --> 00:57:23,816
What the hell are you talking about?

944
00:57:28,863 --> 00:57:30,281
I don't know anything about that.

945
00:57:30,906 --> 00:57:33,450
Gem, after everything we went through,

946
00:57:33,534 --> 00:57:35,744
I know I'm onto something.

947
00:57:37,079 --> 00:57:38,581
I don't know how,

948
00:57:38,664 --> 00:57:41,125
but I feel like everything is connected.

949
00:57:41,208 --> 00:57:44,253
If you don't tell me,
I'll find the answer myself.

950
00:57:53,846 --> 00:57:55,639
<i> I know</i>
<i>where the Veronas are holding</i>

951
00:57:55,723 --> 00:57:57,725
the people they're
sending overseas illegally.

952
00:57:57,808 --> 00:57:58,934
<i>I've found their hideout.</i>

953
00:57:59,018 --> 00:58:00,352
- <i>Hey!</i>
- Run!

954
00:58:02,897 --> 00:58:04,106
You need to leave.

955
00:58:04,190 --> 00:58:06,317
These people are murderers.

956
00:58:06,400 --> 00:58:07,860
I can take care of myself, Teo.

957
00:58:07,943 --> 00:58:09,612
<i>Ma'am Gem is Yana.</i>

958
00:58:09,695 --> 00:58:11,989
- <i>I told you to stop.</i>
- You already know, huh?

959
00:58:12,072 --> 00:58:14,491
Did that criminal confess already?

960
00:58:14,575 --> 00:58:16,452
You don't know what I'm capable of.

961
00:58:16,535 --> 00:58:20,456
If you hurt me,
I'll expose who you really are... Yana.
